"""
Google Location History – Heatmap + Top-15 Sensitive Pins (Hourly)
Thesis: "Inferring Sensitive Personal Information from Google Location History
         Using Data Visualization Techniques"
Author: Matthijs Hagedoorn

=== HOW TO USE ===

1. Export your Google Location History as a single JSON file.
   For instructions on how to do this, see:
   https://support.google.com/maps/answer/6258979?hl=en&co=GENIE.Platform%3DAndroid

2. Set JSON_FILE in CONFIGURATION below to the path of your exported JSON file.

3. Adjust START_DATE and END_DATE to your desired date range.

4. Run the script:
       python GH_location_heatmap_pins_with_information.py

5. Open the output file in a browser (no local server needed):
       thesis_visualizations/location_heatmap_pins_with_information.html

=== OUTPUT ===

  Two layers:
    1. Heatmap   — GPS density at each hour (where you typically are)
    2. Top-15 pins — the 15 most-visited locations, with rich popups:
                       - visit count, avg duration, total hours
                       - bar chart: visits by hour of day
                       - bar chart: visits by day of week
                       - manual reclassification panel (color + label picker)

  Weekday / Weekend toggle:
    Switch between Mon-Fri and Sat-Sun hourly aggregates.

=== DEPENDENCIES ===
    pip install pandas numpy
"""

